INSERT INTO vacancy (id, about, broker, hours, location, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl) VALUES ('0bda5f25-65dc-4d97-8837-bce3212bdd7e', 'Digital collaboration with suppliers and customers increases year over year. Being able to do this secure, compliant and efficient in a complex IT and business environment is important for the ASML product, support and development. Are you challenged by acting as a business partner in order to achieve these business objectives while being in control? ASML‚Äôs Risk & Business Assurance (R&BA) department provides state-ofart expertise, insights and assurance which enables ASML to achieve its objectives, while managing business risks in a responsible way. Within R&BA, we are looking for a Product Owner Partner IAM, where Partners are our suppliers and customers. The Product Owner Partner IAM is responsible for shaping, driving and coordinating the IAM capabilities in ASML‚Äôs collaboration with suppliers and customers, with the objective to achieve this in a secure, compliant and efficient way. -Drive Partner IAM by defining the policies, standards and business processes and ensure that risks related to collaboration with suppliers and customers are sufficiently mitigated. -Develop and execute the Partner IAM vision, strategy and roadmap for ASML -Coordinate and align stakeholders and ensure buy-in from the stakeholders in ASML for the Partner IAM vision, strategy and roadmap -Deliver business value via the Product Ownership role for the agile team that runs the Partner IAM services, including the technology that supports these services -Balance and prioritize the demand in alignment with stakeholders Functie-eisen -About 10 year relevant experience in information security -Experience in Identity & Access management is a plus -Working in Agile mode and with the SAFe methodology -Working in a global corporate organization with many stakeholders, internally and externally Competenties -Multi-disciplinary and mu