INSERT INTO vacancy (id, about, broker, hours, location, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl) VALUES ('028243d4-5bb1-42fc-8f31-7790834f46e2', 'Product Owner Data Management - Platform Squad Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 30+ dagen geleden ING ING is searching for a Product Owner Data Management ‚Äì Platform squad ING is redefining banking. What about you? We at ING are pioneers. Our end goal is to unite ING and to achieve a single and best-in-class experience for all customers worldwide. In order to unite, we decided to build a leading European banking platform first, starting with two of our home markets: Belgium and the Netherlands. The close collaboration across the two countries of ING NL and ING BE started in 2018 with the Delivery Organisation, including cross-border Tribes. There has never been a more interesting time to work at ING. We‚Äôre on a journey that is centered around our customers, powered by technology and driven by smart, determined people. Our employees are empowering our customers to stay a step ahead in life and in business. And we‚Äôre proud of that! Would you like to work for a bank where respect, trust, honesty, and responsibility are valued? Are sustainability, caring for others, and thinking ahead all part of your DNA? Do you want to make a real difference for our customers thanks to our agile way of working? (see: https://youtu.be/uXg6hG6FrG0 ) Then read on, because ING might well be just the employer you‚Äôre looking for. We develop the digital bank of the future As part of the development towards a ‚ÄòNext Generation Digital Banking Platform‚Äô, ING is renewing the data management capabilities globally. Early 2019, the tribe Data Management realised, as part of the ‚ÄòUnite programme‚Äô, an integrated data management platform for the Dutch and Belgian organisations: the ‚ÄòData Lake‚Äô. Good governance of this platform is crucial. Together with data owners and data stewards in the organisation, we ensure that data is defined, can be easily exchanged, the data quality is monitored, and the data lake is set up according to security and privacy standards. We provide the data to important users like Finance, Risk, Analytics, and ING Group. The cross-border ‚Äòbuilding block‚Äô tribe Data Management fulfills a crucial role for all tribes in the Netherlands and Belgium. The tribe operates from three countries, with locations in Amsterdam (NL), Brussels (BE), and Bucharest (RO). The people in our squads come from many different cultural backgrounds. For one of our ‚ÄòPlatform‚Äô squads, we are looking for an enthusiastic Product Owner with knowledge and experience in platform management. This squad has a cross-border (Belgium and The Netherlands) responsibility to deliver and maintain the platform for the Unite data lake to enable the tribe Data Management to meet the demand for the onboarding of data. Your role: You define the requirements for the platform with architects and stakeholders from business and IT. You develop a product vision together with your squad. You assess the feasibility of the proposed solutions. You evaluate the user experiences with the developed solutions and define proposals for improvement. You prioritise the backlog by defining roadmaps in ‚ÄòQuarterly Business Reviews‚Äô, by aligning in ‚ÄòMarketplaces‚Äô with senior management and other Product Owners of the tribe, and by liaising with several departments of ING Group. You secure the operational performance of the assets which are delivered and maintained by your squad. You define and prioritise the operational requirements and organise with your squad the operational tasks to be completed. You continuously take the initiative to improve the way of work and the collaboration within your squad. You frequently align with the Tribe Lead, Product Area Leads, and IT Area Lead, as well as (Chief) Product Owners, Chapter Leads, and Agile Coaches. You work in close collaboration w