INSERT INTO vacancy (id, about, broker, hours, location, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl) VALUES ('83507ddb-0b70-4bac-bfe9-49e620b81642', 'Your challenge will be to develop software for our Philips Interventional Cloud advanced development prototypes and releases: a solution for cloud-based data storage and imaging for minimally invasive treatment of patients. In particular, you will work on the education applications, which are Windows-based C++ and C# applications and simulators. In these applications, you reuse existing software solutions and combine them with advanced simulators in a cloud-hosted Windows environment. You will work as a member of the advanced development project team. Functie-eisen Your responsibilities: ‚Ä¢ Design, test, develop, deploy, maintain and improve software assets for cloud-based education services ‚Ä¢ Deliver high-quality code through hands-on development with attention to detail ‚Ä¢ Analyze/Research issues and provide solutions to quickly resolve them ‚Ä¢ Actively participate in solution design with system engineers and architects ‚Ä¢ Work within the agile/scrum software development team throughout the whole development cycle ensuring built-in quality. ‚Ä¢ You will create the required documentation Your team: You will work within the IGT System Innovation department in Best the Netherlands. The Innovation department is responsible for defining and testing new business propositions and the creation of prototypes to support and test these propositions. You will be working closely with our cloud advanced development project team consisting of 6 engineers working according to the Agile Scrum methodology. We work in an open culture where everyone‚Äôs opinion counts. We strongly believe in providing quality solutions for our customers. We continuously drive improvements in our products and in our processes. You will report to the project leader of the cloud advanced development team. Competenties We are looking for someone with: ‚Ä¢ Bachelor/ Master degree in relevant discipline. ‚Ä¢ 1 year of relevant experience in developing software applications ‚Ä¢ C++, Windows knowledge ‚Ä¢ pragmatic attitude to combine existing software with newly developed simulators ‚Ä¢ Experience within an Agile/SCRUM development environment; able to act as a Software Developer in the different team activities related to the Scrum methodology. ‚Ä¢ Experience with working in a small development team working towards one common goal. ‚Ä¢ Strong communication skills in English and Dutch; a good listener; able to influence others without authority. ‚Ä¢ Working location is at home and on-site in Best. Arbeidsvoorwaarden Our offer We welcome you to our team responsible for the cloud advanced development project. You will work on high-end medical software applications together with your direct colleagues securing product quality for the prototypes and released products as well as further extending its functionality. In this team, you will not only further develop your development skills but also your knowledge in the medical domain of minimally invasive interventional systems. Solliciteren Inclusiviteit en diversiteit Uiteraard staat deze vacature open voor iedereen die zich hierin herkent. We geloven dat diverse teams van belang zijn voor ons als lerende organisatie, die voorop wil blijven lopen in de wereld van werk. Want juist verschillen tussen mensen zorgen voor groei. Van collega''s, klanten, kandidaten en daarmee van Yacht. Heb jij een uniek talent? We ontmoeten je graag. Geerd op 17 augustus 2020Vacaturenummer: 9083706', 'Yacht', '40 uur', 'Best', '17 augustus 2020', null, 'Software Engineer/Developer (Junior/Mid-level)', '9083706', 'https://www.yacht.nl/vacatures/9083706/software-engineer-developer-%28junior-mid-level%29');
