INSERT INTO vacancy (id, about, broker, hours, location, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl) VALUES ('96f643e2-a87c-49c9-b4f1-9ea50a93312e', 'Technical Web Analyst Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Amsterdam 18 augustus PVH The Team The Ecommerce team is responsible for managing the European owned-and-operated tommy.com and calvinklein.com sites across all European markets. The team executes all necessary functions to manage the Ecommerce business end-to-end. Both brands are growing at a rapid pace and have very ambitious growth targets for the coming years. The team is 115+ people strong and will expand significantly by the end of the year. Our team consists of highly motivated and skilled professionals from various cultural backgrounds and nationalities, making it an inspiring environment to work in. As the own-and-operated Ecommerce business is one of the main growth opportunities for both brands, there is a high focus in the organization to support the Ecommerce expansion. The Position The Technical Web Analyst, as part of the Ecommerce Analytics team helps us achieve seamless data quality in order to perform high impact analysis. Day to day, you will be responsible for collecting and integrating data, ensuring data sanity and complete data availability. In addition, you will assist with data integration related projects when necessary and implement tracking and tagging to create a complete dataset. Along with the wider team, you will enable key stakeholders to measure their performance and provide them with clear dashboards and reports. The purpose of the role is to challenge and educate business owners to have a data driven approach, ask the right questions and act upon data insights. Key Responsibilities: ‚Ä¢ Plan, develop and manage web tracking ‚Ä¢ Work directly with developers, business owners across brands and teams to plan and execute tagging and tracking for site analytics ‚Ä¢ Remain in constant contact with stakeholders to ensure no new developments or changes are left untracked ‚Ä¢ Develop necessary codes and ensure implementation ‚Ä¢ Troubleshoot and debug analytics implementations ‚Ä¢ Ensure data integrity & documentation of tracking standards ‚Ä¢ Perform regular analysis to ensure data alignment and explain differences between data sources ‚Ä¢ Identify and solve potential issues ‚Ä¢ Work closely with the PVH Business Intelligence team and external consultant counterparts to help drive our efforts of building a consolidated, single view of customers The Ideal Candidate ‚Ä¢ 2-3 years‚Äô experience in a similar role ideally in an Ecommerce environment ‚Ä¢ University degree from a leading business school/ university ‚Ä¢ Very strong experience with tag management systems (Tealium, Google Tag Manager) ‚Ä¢ Web analytics experience using Google & Adobe Analytics ‚Ä¢ Experience with data visualization tools (Tableau, Data Studio‚Ä¶) ‚Ä¢ Business-level English ‚Ä¢ SQL, SAP BW, Google Cloud, Google Big Query, Optimizely experience is a plus ‚Ä¢ Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with strong presentation capabilities ‚Ä¢ Extremely detail oriented and organized, able to multitask and meet deadlines ‚Ä¢ Self-starter, fast learner, and strong team player Nice-to-haves: ‚Ä¢ Previous experience in Ecommerce fashion / lifestyle ‚Ä¢ Developer background; Java, HTML What you can expect from us ‚Ä¢ A beautiful state-of-the-art Campus, complete with our very own People''s Place Gym and People''s Place Caf√©s ‚Ä¢ A company culture that fosters development, offering training and learning opportunities through our very own PVH University ‚Ä¢ An international environment which respects diversity, equality, and individuality ‚Ä¢ A smart work program that empowers our associates to work at their preferred location within a flexible schedule ‚Ä¢ A chance to unwind with weekly social activities We‚Äôd love to know why this is the role for you, so please include a motivational letter with your application! NOTE: This job description is not intended to be all-inclusive. Employee may perform other related duties as negotiated to meet the ongoing needs of the organization. Amsterdam Noord-Holland ICT Manager Consultant Business intelligence Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Of solliciteer later Dit is geen correct e-mailadres. Vul a.u.b. alle velden in. Bewijs dat je geen robot bent. Er is iets misgegaan bij het versturen van de e-mail. Probeer het nog eens. Je e-mail is verzonden. Jouw e-mailadres Doorsturen PVH', 'Jobbird', '0', 'Amsterdam', '2020-08-18', null, 'Technical Web Analyst', null, 'https://www.jobbird.com/nl/vacature/10453162-technical-web-analyst');
INSERT INTO vacancy (id, about, broker, hours, location, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl) VALUES ('2e256398-1e6d-48d9-951f-02b6fd5046fb', 'Traineeship - IT October 2020 Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 30+ dagen geleden ING The world of banking is changing faster than ever, enjoy the best international experience in our IT traineeship During our four year programme, you create your own career within Information Technology. You learn more about your chosen discipline and about the complex IT environment within ING. Our International Talent programme also allows you to discover yourself through a wide selection of trainings tailored to your needs. Make an impact as a trainee At ING we are always broadening our horizons. Our people have a forward-thinking mentality, a strong can-do spirit and enjoy working in an agile environment. Do you want to have an impact on not only the financial lives of close to 8 million customers but also on the bank of the future? Why wait, discover how today. As an IT trainee you can choose from a number of important IT projects, within which you will make a significant contribution. Now more than ever, IT is the beating heart of ING. Terms such as artificial intelligence, fintech, blockchain, cloud, continuous delivery, API and full stack and have become part of the bank‚Äôs standard vocabulary with good reason. We have 6,6 million customers who make use of online banking, and our mobile app is among the top ten most popular apps. All departments within our organization, such as the dealing room, work with state-of-the-art software which we develop in-house. Your first rotation ING takes a customer-centric approach and IT plays a crucial role in that, which is why we are looking for trainees with a real passion for IT. Based on your own interests, you can indicate your preferences for your first rotation so that we can work together to find a suitable starting role for you. You could set to work as DevOps Engineer, IT Security Engineer, Architect, Java Developer or in the area of Cyber security, for example. These are all projects at the cutting edge of IT and business, with an emphasis on IT. Your benefits Needless to say we offer you an excellent base salary for this traineeship (starters position), a 13th month, paid annual leave, an impressive training package and a permanent contract. But above all we offer you the chance to shape your own ideas about banking in a receptive environment and hence to make banking even simpler and more transparent for our customers. Together with other (international) trainees you will participate in global events, which will enable you to quickly build up a large network. You also have the opportunity to do one of your projects abroad ‚Äì because six months in the likes of Singapore, Sidney or Madrid is not only really interesting but also good for your development. As a trainee you receive guidance from your line manager and your Key Potential Expert (trainee manager). If you are looking for additional guidance you can ask a Senior Manager to mentor you. They will coach you, inspire you, introduce you to their network and share their knowledge and insights with you. Our IT trainee Has a master degree from a university, preferably in Computer Science, Informatics, Software/Computer Engineering or Mathematics (with clear programming affinity). Has a demonstrable and indomitable passion for IT. Is enthusiastic and consider the interests of our customers and your colleagues. Has an innovative take on banking and an unconditional drive to turn your ideas into reality. Has have an interest to learn more about banking/finance Do you have what it takes? When applying for the IT traineeship October 2020, carefully check the dates of the selection rounds below (HR interview and Business Panel). So if you are sure you are what we are looking for, go for it! Deadline for your application: 14 July HR Interviews: 3 August -